  "text": "To characterize cellular changes associated with the ataxia present in 4-week old MIM EX15 mice, we examined the dendritic tree of individual biocytin injected Purkinje neurons (Fig 3A) . Purkinje neuron dendritic arbor collapse has been observed in several SCA models including SCA1 (2), SCA5 (3), while many other models have shown thinned molecular layer including SCA2(1), SCA3 [CITATION_1] , that likely reflects reduced Purkinje dendritic volume. Similarly, MIM EX15 mutants showed a 60% reduction in the expansiveness of the dendritic tree ( Fig 3B) and a significant decrease in the number of dendritic spines (Fig 3C) , although no significant difference was detected in spine length ( Fig 3D) or width (Fig 3E) .",
